cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on virtual machine migration planning in software-defined networks, which involves network resource allocation and routing control. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with optimization problems and proposes a mixed integer programming formulation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes an approximation algorithm, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
